===Etymology===
{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} considered this word to be of {{der|zh|sit}} origin and a cognate to {{cog|my|ရေ||to count}}, {{cog|kfk|ri||to count}}, {{cog|bo|རྩི||to count; to calculate}}, and {{m|bo|རྩིས་པ|t=astronomer}}; however, STEDT derives {{cog|my|ရေ}} & {{cog|bo|རྩི}} from {{cog|sit-pro|*r-tsjəj||to count}} and does not compare them to Chinese [[歷]].
:One derivative is {{och-l|曆|tr=*rêk}}, meaning "calendrical calculations" ({{w|Book of Documents|Shu}}) → "calendar";
:Another derivative is [[exopassive]] {{och-l|麗|tr=*rê(k)h}}, meaning "what is calculated → number" ({{w|Classic of Poetry|Shi}}), whose possible [[allofam]] is {{och-l|麗|tr=*rêh}}.

